## Preparing the Element

While the element is hiding in memory, let's decorate it. We can add text, classes, and IDs using the same Modifiers we learned earlier!

```javascript
let newPara = document.createElement("p");

// Add text and simple styling!
newPara.textContent = "I am born!";
newPara.classList.add("blue-error-text");
```

The element is now fully decorated, but it is *still invisible*.

## Attaching it to Reality

To make our element visible, we MUST 'append' (attach) it to an existing element that is already rendering on the DOM.

We usually target the main Container div, and use **`.appendChild()`**.

```javascript
// 1. Target the existing visual container block
let feedContainer = document.querySelector("#twitter-feed");

// 2. We built 'newPara' on the slide above.

// 3. Shove our new memory element into the visual DOM tree!
feedContainer.appendChild(newPara);
```

Instantly, the paragraph appears on the webpage! You just created life! 🐣
